{{Quote|After 300 years on Corellia, Gowix Computers, which produces a variety of computers for industrial and consumer use, is transferring its corporate character from Corellia to Corulag.|''[[Corellia Times]]'', Basic Edition, 36:7:8 GrS|<ref name="Journal 7" />}}
'''Gowix Computers''' was a [[Computer/Legends|computer]]-manufacturing company headquartered on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Corellia/Legends|Corellia]] for much of its history. Founded sometime before [[300 BBY/Legends|300 BBY]], it was acquired as a subsidiary of the [[Tagge Company/Legends|Tagge Company]] in the [[Standard year/Legends|years]] before the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]], and Gowix became a staunch supporter of the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]] and later the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]], under its new parent company. However, [[Privateer/Legends|privateer]] raids sanctioned by the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Alliance to Restore the Republic]] during the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]] eventually forced [[Chief Executive Officer/Legends|Chief Executive Officer]] [[Gohn Danfeil]] to relocate the company to the planet [[Corulag/Legends|Corulag]].

==History==
{{Quote|We've been contemplating the move for quite some time. For the past few years it has grown ever more difficult to maintain our shipping schedules with less actual traffic passing through the Corellia sector. Our own freighters have of course been shipping our materials and products, but we can't control the shipping infrastructure, and to be perfectly frank, the Coronet Space Port has entered a rapid decline, to say nothing of the spaceports elsewhere in the sector.|CEO Gohn Danfell in a press release|<ref name="Journal 7" />}}
A [[Computer/Legends|computer]] and software-manufacturing company that provided products for industrial and consumer use, Gowix Computers was in operation by at least [[300 BBY/Legends|300 BBY]], by which [[Time/Legends|time]] they were headquartered on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Corellia/Legends|Corellia]].<ref name="Journal 7" /> Sometime after its founding, it was acquired by the [[Tagge Company/Legends|Tagge Company]], a corporation that also owned companies such as [[Bonadan Heavy Industries]] and [[Trast Heavy Transports/Legends|Trast Heavy Transports]].<ref name="Journal 2" /> When the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]] was embroiled in the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]] against the [[Confederacy of Independent Systems/Legends|Confederacy of Independent Systems]] in [[22 BBY/Legends|22 BBY]], Gowix Computers and the other subsidiaries of TaggeCo followed [[Baroness/Legends|Baroness]] [[Sanya Tagge/Legends|Sanya Tagge]] and the rest of TaggeCo in remaining loyal to the Republic,<ref name="Holonet" /> and with the rise of the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]] after the Clone Wars, Gowix was among TaggeCo's subsidiaries that helped the [[House of Tagge/Legends|House of Tagge]] establish a reputation as a major supplier to both the Empire and the [[Corporate Sector/Legends|Corporate Sector]].<ref name="Pirates">''[[Pirates & Privateers]]''</ref> By [[1 ABY/Legends|1 ABY]], the company was headed by [[Chief Executive Officer/Legends|Chief Executive Officer]] [[Gohn Danfeil]], who made the decision to transfer Gowix's corporate charter to the planet [[Corulag/Legends|Corulag]] when the [[Corellian sector/Legends|Corellian sector]] began to lose much of its commercial traffic due to an unstable economy and [[Pirate/Legends|pirate]] attacks during the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]].<ref name="Journal 7" /> Gowix Computers was among the companies whose vessels were targeted by [[Privateer/Legends|privateers]] on the behalf of the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Alliance to Restore the Republic]], as its parent company TaggeCo's support of the Empire presented an opportunity for the Alliance to disrupt the Empire's commerce.<ref name="Pirates" />

==Behind the scenes==
Gowix Computers was first mentioned in the [[1994]] [[Star Wars Adventure Journal 2|second issue]] of the [[West End Games]] role-playing magazine ''[[Star Wars Adventure Journal]]'', as a potential target for Alliance privateers in the adventure ''[[Rebel Privateers!]]''.<ref name="Journal 2" /> It later appeared a year later in the [[Star Wars Adventure Journal 7|seventh issue]], where the [[Galaxywide NewsNets]] portion of the journal featured a press release by the ''[[Corellia Times]]'' on Gowix's move to Corulag.<ref name="Journal 7" /> Another adventure in the same issue, ''[[Into the Core Worlds]]'', mentioned Gowix as a major high-tech firm on the planet of Corulag.<ref name="Core">{{JournalCite|7|Into the Core Worlds}}</ref> The role-playing supplement ''[[Pirates & Privateers]]'', published in [[1997]], again mentioned Gowix as a potential target for privateers.<ref name="Pirates" /> Gowix received another mention in the [[2005]] reference book ''[[The New Essential Guide to Droids]]'', appearing in the entry for TaggeCo as one of its subsidiaries,<ref name="NEGTD">''[[The New Essential Guide to Droids]]''</ref> and [[HoloNet News Vol. 531 49|issue #49 of the 531st]] volume of the in-universe [[HoloNet News (original website)|HoloNet News]] again mentioned Gowix as a subsidiary of TaggeCo.<ref name="Holonet" /> The [[2012]] [[Star Wars video games|video game]] ''[[Star Wars: The Old Republic]]'', set over 3,600 [[Standard year/Legends|years]] before the Adventure Journals, introduced a [[Gowix Corporation]] on Corellia, but so far no connection has been made between the two companies.<ref name="Firestorm">{{TORcite|type=class|Jedi Knight|Firestorm|Corellia}}</ref>

